      contentEn:
          'The Human Trafficking and Transportation Act 2007 addresses the prevention and suppression of human trafficking in Nepal. It criminalizes trafficking for sexual exploitation, forced labor, organ removal, and other forms of exploitation. The act provides for strict punishments including life imprisonment for traffickers. It also includes provisions for victim protection, rehabilitation, and compensation. The act established a National Committee to coordinate anti-trafficking efforts.',
